(exping that is).  Main reason being if you don't know what you are doing, you will get yourself killed.<br>
<br>
I Quaded these from 58-60 and it is by far the best exp out there.  They don't have to many hp and aren't all that resistant.<br>
<br>
Sounds easy so far right?<br>
<br>
Well here is the tricky part,  the shaman cast sow on the warriors(these will be what you want the warriors) and haste.  In other words unless you pull properly you will have a hasted otter beating the crap out of you.<br>
<br>
Now I suggest while you learn the curve that you have a nearby druid cast sow on you.(Once you learn jboot are fine).<br>
<br>
Pulling - As a wizard without harmony you are going to want to avoid the center camp because the chief will kick the crap out of you.  This leaves you 2 camps, both with 4 warriors each, you can really only handle one.  Ok, if you do the camp nearest to SS(the one with the 2 named that aren't merchants) then all you do is pull them with snare, round them up and then group snare them.. easy enough.<br>
  For the other camp with the merchants, first cast annul on the otter in SE corner of camp then snare him when he is away, then snare pull the other 3(reason being you WILL get a merchant if you do not do it this way).<br>
<br>
Alright, what do you do if you get a snare resist?(this WILL happen).  Couple things.  If you have good MR then what I did was simply snare them while they were hitting me.<br>
If you do not have good MR, then root snare, and round up the rest while you wait for root to break.(Best to just get decent MR).<br>
<br>
I used bonds of force because it takes less mana and also I would pretty much always resist it if I cast it on one while it was hitting me.<br>
<br>
Pillar of Lightining works fine, I think any 3 of your pillars would.<br>
<br>
If you get a shelfish collector don't panic, simply root it and continue on your kite.<br>
<br>
To anyone who has never been to CS before there are drakes with a very very nasty AE with a very large radius.  It will do a nice chunk of damage to you as well as dispell.   LUCKILY for YOU verant made it where the drake aes no longer will effect the otters.  What does that mean? 2 things.  1 - the damn drakes won't dispell you otters snare(had that happen).  2 the fewl druids who get drake adds and run them to the beach for help from the otters both get to die and also the otters won't train around the beach(DIE DRUIDS).<br>
<br>
So really, the otters are not to diffuclt, just use caution, I always med invis but hopefully you do also.<br>
<br>
Perks - otters drop some decent armor, quest gems and fur.<br>
If you plan on doing the 10th shawl quest like myself I suggest you save the fur.  =/ I gave all mine away to tailoring friends thinking I would never need the ghey skill then verant adds a kick ass quest that use's it heh.<br>
<br>
If you aren't kos to dragons you can bind at os and gate there for c2 etc and then port right back to cs.<br>
<br>
Otters aren't overcamped and you can pretty much always do them.  I have yet to see another wizard on the Nameless server quading them.  Only downside is you can't do there ghey quests.<br>
<br>
Soren<br>
