<br>
I've done the otters for 4 days in 59 now, and am 3 blue bubbles in. I've died a few times but they were stupid mistakes and they shouldn't be happening anymore.<br>
<br>
My attack plan is as follows.<br>
<br>
Sit above camp on cliff watching till all 4 spawn.<br>
Cast levitate and float down.<br>
Snare Otter close to named, snare one closest to him on the right.<br>
Walk around and snare the one farthest to the right.<br>
Run back a little ways, cast improved invis. (To avoid shellfish collector)<br>
Run around till I'm perpendicular to the 4th one, snare it.<br>
Run back a ways so that I make sure none of the otters when I run up the cliff run past the two named (last time it happended I had quarry tasting my liver).<br>
Then just run up the cliff, and med for a few till they show up.<br>
Then its just as simple as re-snaring, then kiting them up and down the pleatue.<br>
<br>
I can med my mana back full and have a 3-4 minute wait before they respawn and with clarity I usually try the other camp in my downtime.<br>
<br>
Instead of pulling with dispell magic though, I pulled with my flux staff from as far back as possible, and just started casting atols as soon as the otters in range. If I got no fizzles the snare would hit him before he got close enought to me.<br>
<br>
Shellfish collectors are your worst enemy. Yet, on the far camp some of them don't get close enough to the shamans to be sowed so your ass isn't always cooked.<br>
<br>
The good news is its basicly the best thing to quad at 59, your right next to a bank and merchants in SS, and loot is pretty good for something as simple as otters.<br>
<br>
Bad news, faction would have been nice to keep, resists hurt, and half are green with the 50% exp hit.<br>
